1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,087
[Marcus] <i>You're the ones destroying</i>
<i>the police's reputation.</i>

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,590
<i>I'll make you pay for all your sins.</i>

3
00:00:08,883 --> 00:00:11,177
[man] <i>Ma'am, we're under attack here!</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:12,429
Where are you?

5
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:14,222
I'm glad you finally asked for my help.

6
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:16,433
Hurry up! We can't let Datu Rahman escape!

7
00:00:17,308 --> 00:00:18,268
Jalil?

8
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:21,187
- [Datu Rahman] How did you get here?!
- We have to go.

9
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:22,313
I'll explain everything later.

10
00:00:22,397 --> 00:00:24,232
[Usman] <i>There were armed men</i>

11
00:00:24,315 --> 00:00:26,443
<i>who took Datu Rahman from the safe house.</i>

12
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:29,446
- What?!
- I'm looking for them now.

13
00:00:29,529 --> 00:00:31,990
[Marcus] <i>Alright, brother,</i>
<i>try to find them.</i>

14
00:00:32,073 --> 00:00:33,825
<i>I'm on my way back.</i>

15
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:35,160
[Jalil] <i>Father, let's go!</i>

16
00:00:35,243 --> 00:00:36,453
Don't move!

17
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:38,663
[Usman] <i>Who are you? What do you want</i>
<i>from Datu Rahman?!</i>

18
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,790
- Major…
- [Jalil] <i>I'm not Espina.</i>

19
00:00:40,874 --> 00:00:43,293
- I am Jalil.
- Give back Datu Rahman!

20
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:46,212
You know that he's innocent.
That's why you hid him, right?

21
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:49,215
[Jalil] <i>You don't even trust</i>
<i>your own comrades in NLEA.</i>

22
00:00:49,299 --> 00:00:53,011
My father's in danger as long
as I haven't taken him into hiding.

23
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:53,970
Please.

24
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:55,972
[in Tausug] Thank you.

25
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:59,059
[Datu Rahman] Why did the officer
call you Major Allan Espina?

26
00:00:59,142 --> 00:01:01,936
I put on a different identity to find you

27
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:05,440
and to find who is responsible
for all of this.

28
00:01:05,523 --> 00:01:06,900
[Jalil] <i>Father,</i>
<i>it's because of that island</i>

29
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:09,861
<i>that I received my name,</i>
<i>I developed my identity,</i>

30
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:13,114
<i>and most importantly,</i>
<i>I got to have a family.</i>

31
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:14,574
So I'm not going to stop

32
00:01:14,657 --> 00:01:17,994
until I find out who did this to us.

33
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:20,955
[Jalil] <i>We will take back everything</i>
<i>they took from us.</i>

34
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:31,841
[mysterious theme music playing]

35
00:01:42,727 --> 00:01:46,356
[stirring music playing]

36
00:02:04,874 --> 00:02:08,837
[stirring music continues]

37
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,754
‪[Lara sighs]

38
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:15,385
[frustrated scream]

39
00:02:17,929 --> 00:02:18,847
Madam!

40
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:51,254
[stirring music continues]

41
00:03:16,112 --> 00:03:17,155
[gun thuds]

42
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:20,033
[screams]

43
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:34,881
- I know who did this.
- Who?!

44
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,800
[Felix] Here.

45
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:39,844
Datu Rahman's son.

46
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,139
My men have already caught him.

47
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:46,142
He's the one who attacked Zylverix.

48
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,810
But he escaped.

49
00:03:48,436 --> 00:03:49,270
He's slippery.

50
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,527
Madam!

51
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:58,696
[Felix sighs]

52
00:04:01,699 --> 00:04:02,575
[Jamilah sighs]

53
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:04,244
Where is Jalil?

54
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:06,120
[Jamilah exhales]

55
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:08,706
Don't worry. I'm sure they're near.

56
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:09,999
‪[Omar breathes deeply]

57
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,170
[rapid knocking on door]

58
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:15,713
[door creaks open]

59
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,467
[Norhana crying]

60
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:21,135
- Jalil!
- [Omar] It's Jalil.

61
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:22,720
Jamilah?

62
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,472
Allah…

63
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:25,390
‪[somber music playing]

64
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,476
[door clicks shut]

65
00:04:29,435 --> 00:04:30,395
Father?

66
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:32,397
My daughter.

67
00:04:34,649 --> 00:04:36,734
[Datu Rahman, Jamilah crying]

68
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:41,906
[Jamilah inhales sharply]

69
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:43,866
[Datu Rahman] My daughter…

70
00:04:46,619 --> 00:04:48,871
[crying]

71
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:51,124
[Omar] Rahman.

72
00:04:55,545 --> 00:05:00,049
[indistinct]

73
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:00,967
‪[all crying]

74
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:07,265
[somber music playing]

75
00:05:19,235 --> 00:05:20,528
Find Datu Rahman!

76
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:22,155
I don't care how you do it.

77
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,698
You want to make me happy, don't you?

78
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:25,783
[in English] Bring him back to me!

79
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:29,078
[dramatic sting]

80
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:31,956
[in English] Okay, madam.

81
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:34,500
I'll take care of it.

82
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:43,718
[car engine starts]

83
00:06:00,943 --> 00:06:06,157
[pensive music playing]

84
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,916
I can't lie to Marcus.

85
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:22,090
[pensive music continues]

86
00:06:31,307 --> 00:06:32,141
‪[music intensifies]

87
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:38,689
Sir Ahmad Mustapha?

88
00:06:43,653 --> 00:06:44,529
‪[music concludes]

89
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,077
Father.

90
00:06:52,328 --> 00:06:54,539
Do you know who did this to you?

91
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:58,042
How many times did they abduct you?

92
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,545
Father, what do they need from you?

93
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:03,506
[pensive music playing]

94
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:08,177
I don't know, son.

95
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:11,264
I don't know them.

96
00:07:13,057 --> 00:07:15,351
I don't know why they're doing this.

97
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,520
Okay.

98
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:20,231
Alright, uh…

99
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:22,692
Get some rest, okay?

100
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:24,902
Get some rest.

101
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:27,613
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you,

102
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:28,948
SPO1,

103
00:07:29,031 --> 00:07:31,492
Usman Sabdani.

104
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,161
[in Arabic] And upon you be peace.

105
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:34,328
Sir.

106
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:38,458
- What do you need from me?
- I need to talk to you.

107
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,918
It's important.

108
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:43,296
About Jalil Abubakar.

109
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,883
You need to help him.

110
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:48,676
You need to protect him.

111
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,136
What?

112
00:07:50,678 --> 00:07:52,263
I gave Jalil

113
00:07:53,055 --> 00:07:55,141
a mission in NLEA.

114
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:58,728
I turned him into Allan Espina.

115
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:03,107
[pensive music playing]

116
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,233
What's the mission?

117
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:06,027
[in Arabic] I'll relay it to you.

118
00:08:07,945 --> 00:08:09,655
But you can only know

119
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:12,158
the information I can share.

120
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:13,826
Nothing more.

121
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:15,953
Usman…

122
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,247
What's happening now

123
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,626
is bigger than all of us.

124
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,545
I need your cooperation.

125
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:26,547
Usman…

126
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:32,261
You can't tell anyone the true identity

127
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:34,430
of Major Allan Espina,

128
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,724
not even to your friend, Marcus.

129
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:40,770
[pensive music continues]

130
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,230
- But, sir--
- Usman.

131
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:46,400
You need to help Allan Espina.

132
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:48,986
You need to help Jalil in his mission.

133
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:52,240
Can I count on you, brother?

134
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:53,616
‪[dramatic sting]

135
00:08:58,079 --> 00:09:00,665
[sighs] I'll get going now.

136
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:01,958
I have to go.

137
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,418
Please take care of Father.

138
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:07,463
Of course. We won't abandon him.

139
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,090
And we will keep your secret.

140
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:11,968
[Norhana] Jalil, be careful, okay?

141
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:14,303
The people chasing you are dangerous.

142
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:17,848
‪[somber music playing]

143
00:09:19,934 --> 00:09:21,060
Auntie…

144
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:23,938
[in Tausug] Thank you.

145
00:09:26,023 --> 00:09:27,024
[Norhana muttering]

146
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:28,693
[in Tausug] Thank you.

147
00:09:28,776 --> 00:09:29,902
[smooches, sniffles]

148
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,037
- Uncle, look after my father.
- I will.

149
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:43,791
- I'll leave him to you.
- We won't abandon him.

150
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:45,710
[Jalil inhales]

151
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:49,255
[Jalil inhales]

152
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:52,300
Jalil, be careful.

153
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:54,844
I will be waiting for your call.

154
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,514
Jamilah, yes.

155
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,267
Don't worry.

156
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:06,022
Don't worry. Everything will be okay.

157
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:08,691
The truth will soon come out.

158
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:12,153
Jamilah… [sniffs]

159
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,363
Take care of Father, okay?

160
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,365
Protect him.

161
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:19,368
[Jalil sniffles]

162
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:21,120
[in Arabic] In the name of Allah.

163
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,460
[Jalil sniffling]

164
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:30,421
- [Jamilah] Be careful.
- [Norhana] Be careful, Jalil.

165
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:32,632
[Norhana crying]

166
00:10:32,715 --> 00:10:37,345
[somber music playing]

167
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:40,097
- [Jalil gasps]
- [Jamilah cries]

168
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:43,351
[Datu Rahman] Jalil, my son…

169
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:46,812
[crying]

170
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:53,694
[ominous music playing]

171
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,671
Father.

172
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:14,799
‪[gentle music playing]

173
00:11:14,882 --> 00:11:15,883
Thank you.

174
00:11:16,550 --> 00:11:18,052
[Jamilah exhales, sniffles]

175
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:23,099
Father…

176
00:11:25,434 --> 00:11:27,436
What did they do to you?

177
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,025
Where did they take you?

178
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:38,239
Did they hurt you?

179
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:39,907
[hushed] No.

180
00:11:40,616 --> 00:11:42,284
No, Jamilah.

181
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:43,869
- I'm fine, I'm fine.
- But, Father…

182
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:47,498
Who did this to you?
Why did they hide you?

183
00:11:48,999 --> 00:11:51,252
What do they need from you, Father?

184
00:11:52,002 --> 00:11:53,045
I don't know either.

185
00:11:53,129 --> 00:11:55,214
- But Father--
- Jamilah.

186
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:59,468
The important thing is that I am here.

187
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:02,430
We're together again.

188
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:03,764
[Jamilah sniffles]

189
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:09,562
Father, let's go back to the island.

190
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:11,939
Let's go back to our old lives.

191
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:13,691
To our peaceful old lives.

192
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:15,025
[Datu Rahman grunts]

193
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:18,279
Not yet, my dear.

194
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:21,282
We will go back one day.

195
00:12:21,365 --> 00:12:22,533
‪[sobs]

196
00:12:22,616 --> 00:12:27,496
But we still have
unfinished business here.

197
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:30,708
So when we return to the island,

198
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:34,795
no one will ever come after us again.

199
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:40,468
[pensive music playing]

200
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:47,516
- [Jamilah sobs softly]
- [Datu Rahman breathes heavily]

201
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,895
I love you so much, Jamilah.

202
00:12:50,978 --> 00:12:53,522
[Jamilah whimpers]

203
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:56,775
- Don't cry, my dear.
- [sniffles]

204
00:12:58,235 --> 00:13:02,156
[Datu Rahman] <i>My silence</i>
<i>will protect my children.</i>

205
00:13:04,992 --> 00:13:08,829
[reciting prayer in Arabic]

206
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,502
[Jalil] <i>Oh, Allah.</i>

207
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:16,962
Thank you.

208
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:22,051
- [poignant music playing]
- [sniffles]

209
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:24,762
[Jalil] <i>Thank you, Allah,</i>
<i>for saving Father.</i>

210
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:30,392
[poignant music continues]

211
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:43,322
[intense music playing]

212
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:48,077
- [thunder rumbling]
- [waves crashing]

213
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,707
[thunder claps]

214
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,086
[breathes heavily]

215
00:14:03,676 --> 00:14:09,014
[ominous music playing]

216
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,480
[Marcus] Ma.

217
00:14:19,775 --> 00:14:20,818
Son.

218
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,404
If you don’t mind me asking,

219
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:24,905
where were you?

220
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:26,198
- [sighs softly]
- [somber music playing]

221
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:27,867
I just got back, Ma.

222
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:33,289
I went to Damai Island to investigate.

223
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:34,582
What happened?

224
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:37,167
Why do you look like that?

225
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:40,504
Ma, I saw Harold.

226
00:14:41,589 --> 00:14:43,299
He's alive.

227
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:44,592
Harold is alive?

228
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:48,220
Where is he? Is he with you?

229
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,473
I had to leave him on the island.

230
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,268
[sighs sharply]

231
00:14:54,351 --> 00:14:56,979
I don't know how to tell his grandmother

232
00:14:57,771 --> 00:14:58,981
that her grandson is alive,

233
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,025
but I can't bring him back

234
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:04,111
because he's shell-shocked.

235
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:06,989
His life will be in danger

236
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:10,784
if anyone at NLEA
finds out he’s still alive.

237
00:15:10,868 --> 00:15:16,332
[morose music playing]

238
00:15:19,335 --> 00:15:20,544
[keypad clacking]

239
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:24,757
[phone ringing]

240
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:27,426
Hello?

241
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:28,719
Who's this?

242
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:30,888
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you, Rashid.

243
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:35,267
Jalil, is that you?

244
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:37,102
Yes.

245
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:40,189
Why'd you call?

246
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:41,523
Is there a problem?

247
00:15:42,066 --> 00:15:42,942
[Jalil] <i>No.</i>

248
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,860
Everything's fine, Rashid.

249
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,780
I just wanted to thank you.

250
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:51,075
If you didn't talk to me,

251
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:53,702
who knows what would've
happened to Father.

252
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:56,789
I don't know what I'd do

253
00:15:56,872 --> 00:15:59,416
if something bad happened to him.

254
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,253
You’ve been a huge help, Rashid.

255
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:06,924
I don’t know how to repay you.

256
00:16:07,007 --> 00:16:10,386
That's not necessary, Jalil.

257
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,471
You and your family are good people.

258
00:16:13,222 --> 00:16:15,140
[Rashid] <i>I just want you to get justice.</i>

259
00:16:15,224 --> 00:16:16,725
You don't owe me anything.

260
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,353
I'm happy to help.

261
00:16:19,436 --> 00:16:22,523
Rashid, you're the reason
I was able to save Father.

262
00:16:23,607 --> 00:16:25,401
[in Tausug] Thank you.

263
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:28,445
Just let me know if you need anything.

264
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,948
I’ll help you the best I can.

265
00:16:31,031 --> 00:16:34,618
[stirring music playing]

266
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:57,307
[music intensifies]

267
00:16:57,391 --> 00:16:58,809
[tires screech]

268
00:17:06,692 --> 00:17:11,405
[dramatic sting]

269
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:25,794
[Usman] <i>They took him.</i>

270
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:28,464
<i>They took Datu Rahman.</i>

271
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:33,635
<i>There were armed men</i>
<i>who abducted Datu Rahman.</i>

272
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,512
[grunts angrily]

273
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:40,350
[tense music continues]

274
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:43,062
[Ramli] You didn't just take Datu Rahman,

275
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,105
you stole our peace!

276
00:17:45,189 --> 00:17:49,026
Now those weapons are everywhere!

277
00:17:51,612 --> 00:17:53,614
[Ramli] <i>We lost our protectors!</i>

278
00:17:54,114 --> 00:17:55,991
Datu Rahman and Jalil!

279
00:17:57,534 --> 00:18:01,038
Now you're after them like criminals.

280
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:07,044
[music concludes]

281
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:09,379
[traffic noise]

282
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:16,762
[pensive music playing]

283
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:20,974
A lot of our men died
trying to arrest you!

284
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:22,976
Why are you so important?!

285
00:18:23,852 --> 00:18:25,813
[Marcus] <i>Who the hell are you?</i>

286
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:28,565
[Jalil] Do you have any idea
who could've done this?

287
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:30,859
They wouldn’t stop
until they captured you.

288
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:34,029
Father, what do they want from you?

289
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:40,077
[pensive music continues]

290
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:45,582
Hasan, are you sure
there are bombs planted here?

291
00:18:46,458 --> 00:18:47,960
The police found out

292
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:49,628
that there's a weapons shipment
hidden here.

293
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:52,756
They're waiting for the boat
to dock at the pier.

294
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,424
So the Colonel planted bombs here

295
00:18:54,508 --> 00:18:56,301
to destroy all the evidence against him.

296
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:58,887
Damn him! That bastard!

297
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,430
A lot of people are going to die!

298
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:02,391
We need to find the bombs,

299
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:03,600
- so we can defuse them
- [panicked breathing]

300
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:05,018
and save everyone here!

301
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:10,232
[Datu Rahman] <i>You're dead already.</i>

302
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,902
<i>Who is doing this?</i>

303
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:17,489
[grim music playing]

304
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:23,370
[tense music playing]

305
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,038
[in English] There.

306
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:28,458
- Follow that van.
- Alright, sir.

307
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:32,337
There it is, sir.

308
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:34,423
It went this way.

309
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:36,717
Then it went there, sir.

310
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,636
It's heading to the shipyard.

311
00:19:48,228 --> 00:19:50,814
Where is it? Where'd it go?

312
00:19:50,898 --> 00:19:52,107
Sir.

313
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:54,651
The CCTV cameras were deactivated.

314
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,653
This must be what they do

315
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:58,280
when something illegal is happening.

316
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:00,115
To cover everything up.

317
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:05,370
This is alarming, Sir Marcus.

318
00:20:08,498 --> 00:20:10,000
[sighs]

319
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:11,752
Someone from the inside did this.

320
00:20:11,835 --> 00:20:14,171
[unsettling music playing]

321
00:20:14,254 --> 00:20:16,715
[vehicles honking]

322
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:27,392
[morose music playing]

323
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:28,435
Bud.

324
00:20:30,103 --> 00:20:31,521
What happened?

325
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:34,983
Did they get away?

326
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:38,153
[Usman] Freeze!

327
00:20:39,529 --> 00:20:42,532
[tense music playing]

328
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:44,785
Bro, there was a fight.

329
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,788
I went toward the gunfire.

330
00:20:48,872 --> 00:20:52,292
Someone took Datu Rahman away
from the abductors.

331
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:54,503
Was he wearing a mask?

332
00:20:58,882 --> 00:21:03,553
[tense music continues]

333
00:21:06,014 --> 00:21:07,599
That's Datu Rahman's son.

334
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,559
Jalil Abubakar.

335
00:21:11,061 --> 00:21:14,022
[Ahmad] You can't tell anyone

336
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:18,151
about Major Allan Espina's true identity.

337
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:20,028
Not even your friend Marcus.

338
00:21:21,446 --> 00:21:27,786
You need to help Jalil fulfill
his mission as Allan Espina.

339
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:31,039
Can I count on you, brother?

340
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:34,501
[tense music continues]

341
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:36,253
Buddy.

342
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:42,009
[tense music swells, fades]

343
00:21:42,092 --> 00:21:43,844
[birds chirping]

344
00:21:47,055 --> 00:21:52,436
[pensive music playing]

345
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:57,607
[sighs]

346
00:22:06,408 --> 00:22:07,576
[sighs]

347
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,622
You…

348
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:16,043
were the only one who accepted me.

349
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:17,169
[sniffles]

350
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:21,465
Even though I was an illegitimate child.

351
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:27,804
Too bad you're not here anymore, Napoleon.

352
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:32,809
[inhales, exhales deeply]

353
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:35,062
Don't worry.

354
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,982
I will make sure

355
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:43,737
that all our dreams come true.

356
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:51,912
Our efforts will not go to waste.

357
00:22:52,496 --> 00:22:55,624
[grim music playing]

358
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:56,541
‪[dramatic sting]

359
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:03,757
[exhales]

360
00:23:04,716 --> 00:23:06,051
[breathes shakily]

361
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:12,099
[grim music continues]

362
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,868
Datu Rahman is telling the truth.

363
00:23:31,952 --> 00:23:33,912
They didn't smuggle those weapons.

364
00:23:33,995 --> 00:23:36,665
The syndicate protector is inside NLEA.

365
00:23:36,748 --> 00:23:42,629
Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't suspend you right now!

366
00:23:42,712 --> 00:23:45,674
[man] <i>There's no trace of any fight here.</i>

367
00:23:45,757 --> 00:23:47,217
[Marcus] <i>Keep looking.</i>

368
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:48,593
[Marcus] <i>They covered their tracks.</i>

369
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:52,556
<i>Sweetheart, our son</i>
<i>got into a fight at school.</i>

370
00:23:52,639 --> 00:23:55,684
<i>I’ll fight anyone</i>
<i>who talks badly about you.</i>

371
00:24:00,355 --> 00:24:03,483
Madam, I've identified Datu Rahman's son.

372
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:04,860
His name's Jalil Abubakar.

373
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:06,111
[Lara] <i>How did that happen?</i>

374
00:24:06,194 --> 00:24:09,156
He must have someone helping him.

375
00:24:10,824 --> 00:24:12,033
We need to find him.

376
00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:15,328
Check the CCTV footage from around 10 p.m.

377
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:17,289
near the shipyard exits.

378
00:24:17,372 --> 00:24:18,790
[Buster, in English] <i>Copy, ma'am.</i>

379
00:24:24,671 --> 00:24:27,465
[theme music ends]
